Thornheart Grove
A Skyrim One-Shot Adventure for 5-6 Players (Novice Tier)
Estimated Play Time: 4-5 hours
 Party Size: 5-6 players
 Difficulty: Scaled for Novice Tier
 Reward: Significant gold, nature-themed enchanted items, and 1 Advancement Point

`Adventure Summary
The group's success at Winterhold has earned them a modest reputation as capable sellswords willing to handle dangerous work. Word has reached Maven Black-Briar in Riften, who has need of competent mercenaries for a delicate problem. The ancient Thornheart Grove, a sacred site dedicated to Kynareth, has become corrupted by dark magic. What was once a place of healing and natural beauty is now a twisted maze of aggressive plants and malevolent spirits. The grove's corruption is spreading, choking the life from surrounding forests and threatening Riften's lumber industry. Worse yet, several woodcutters and a priestess of Kynareth have vanished within its thorny embrace.

Part I: Arrival in Riften (The "City" Section) Riften | Skyrim Music and Ambience
Setting the Scene:
"You arrive in Riften, a city of canals and shadows built on the shores of Lake Honrich. The air smells of damp wood and fermenting honey. As you enter, you hear the gentle lapping of water against the wooden walkways and the distant clang of a blacksmith's hammer. The city is alive with hushed, secretive conversations, and you get the sense that a thin veneer of law and order barely conceals the corrupt underworld that is the city's true lifeblood."
What the Players Can Do:
At this point, the players are free to explore. This is where you use the Riften City Profile as your guide.
If they go to the market, they can meet Madesi and discover the side quest.
If they go to the smithy, they can meet Balimund and hear the "Professional's Concern" rumor.
If they go to the Temple of Mara, they can meet Priestess Dinya and hear the "Noble's Whisper" rumor.
If they explore the alleys, they might encounter the shifty Dunmer and hear the "Outlier's Tale" rumor.
If they go to the Bee and Barb, they'll find Torolf (the "Commoner's Fear" rumor) and see a well-dressed woman watching them from a corner tableΓÇöMaven Black-Briar.
The Trigger for the Main Quest:
The main quest begins whenever the players decide to approach the elegant woman in the Bee and Barb.


Part 2: The Bee and Barb Inn (The Hook) Skyrim - Music & Ambience - Taverns
Setting the Scene
The players arrive in Riften to find the city buzzing with talk of their recent heroics at Winterhold. They're directed to The Bee and Barb Inn, where they find an unusually elegant woman waiting for them.
Read Aloud:
"The Bee and Barb Inn has the usual mix of travelers and locals tonight. At a corner table sits an impeccably dressed Nord woman with silver-streaked hair and keen eyes. She wears fine robes of deep green trimmed with goldΓÇöclearly someone of wealth and influence. When she notices your group, she gestures subtly for you to approach. 'You must be the sellswords I've heard aboutΓÇöthe ones who handled that unpleasant business in Winterhold. I am Maven Black-Briar, and I have work that requires... discrete professionals.'"
The Quest Giver: Maven Black-Briar
Maven (Guile 16, Might 10, Magic 12, Agility 14) is a wealthy businesswoman with connections throughout Riften's underworld. She's heard they handled the Winterhold job professionally and needs competent mercenaries for a problem that's hurting her business interests.
What Maven Tells Them:
The Problem: Thornheart Grove, an ancient shrine to Kynareth two hours northeast of Riften, has become "twisted and wrong" in the past month.
Her Interest: Maven's lumber operations depend on the surrounding forest, and the corruption is spreading, threatening her investments.
The Corruption: Trees have grown into unnatural shapes, thorny vines move on their own, and poisonous spores drift through the air. The corruption spreads roughly 100 feet per week.
The Missing: Three woodcutters (Bjorn, Halvard, and Sven) working for her went missing two weeks ago. Priestess Danica, whom Maven hired to investigate, vanished three days ago.
The Offer: Maven will pay 600 gold each to cleanse the grove and bring back any survivors. "I pay well for results, and I reward discretion even better."
Additional Information (if asked):
Thornheart Grove was planted over 1,000 years ago by ancient druids as a sanctuary
Local legend says a Heart Tree at the center channels Kynareth's blessing
The corruption began suddenlyΓÇöone day the grove was normal, the next it was twisted
Maven suspects someone has deliberately cursed the site but doesn't know who
Maven's Hidden Agenda: She doesn't mention that her family has been illegally harvesting rare herbs from the grove for alchemical purposes. She fears the corruption might be connected to their activities.

Part 3: The Road to Thornheart Grove Forests of Autumn | Peaceful Skyrim Music & Ambience | 3 Hours
The Corrupted Forest Edge
As the party travels northeast, the landscape gradually changes from normal autumn forest to something more sinister.
Encounter: The Desperate Woodcutter About halfway to the grove, the party encounters Torolf, a grizzled woodcutter fleeing the area with his cart and oxen.
Torolf (Guile 11, Might 15) is terrified: "Turn back, friends! That place ain't natural no more! I saw Bjorn get dragged into the trees by vines thick as a man's arm. And the sounds... sweet Kynareth, the sounds those trees make at night!"
What They Can Learn:
The three missing woodcutters were working the grove's outer edge when they disappeared
Bjorn was definitely taken aliveΓÇöTorolf heard him screaming for help from deep in the grove
Strange lights (green and purple) pulse from the grove's center at night
The animals have all fled the areaΓÇöeven the birds won't fly overhead
Potential Aid: Torolf has 2 Potions of Cure Poison that he offers freely, saying "You'll need these more than me, and may Kynareth protect you where she couldn't protect my friends."

Part 4: Thornheart Grove - The Living Dungeon Skyrim - Music & Ambience - Dungeons [10 Hours]
Approaching the Grove
Read Aloud:
"The corruption is immediately visible as you approach what should be Thornheart Grove. Where once stood majestic pines and oaks, now twisted trees reach skyward like gnarled claws. Thorny vines as thick as rope writhe slowly across the ground, and the air shimmers with drifting spores that make your eyes water. A sickly green light pulses from somewhere deep within the grove, and you can swear you hear the trees... whispering. The main path, once welcoming, is now choked with aggressive undergrowth that seems to part reluctantly at your approach."

Environmental Effect - The Grove's Corruption:
Poisonous Spores: All characters must make a Might roll every turn or lose 1 FP from inhaling toxic spores, unless mitigated.
Living Terrain: Vines and roots can grab at characters. Any character who fails an Agility roll gets entangled for 1 round.
Unnatural Growth: Fire damage is increased by +1 against plant creatures, but healing magic is reduced by -1 due to the corruption
This encounter also serves as-
