Section 2: The Pilgrim's Path - The Living Maze (Puzzle/Challenge)
How to Use This Schematic
Start: The party begins in 8 (Entrance).
Movement: Only follow the arrows shown on the schematic. If there is no arrow connecting two nodes in a given direction, that path does not exist.
Ex: From Node 8, a path exists to Node 7 (West) and Node 9 (East), but not to Node 5 (North).
The Trigger (The Rule of Disturbance): The maze reconfigures itself after a significant action. Rotate this schematic 90 degrees clockwise whenever a combat encounter concludes OR a player makes any non-combat skill roll (Guile, Magic, etc.).
The Puzzle in Action: Do not announce the rotation. The numbers and connections on your schematic are fixed, but their orientation changes. The players' sense of "North" is always the direction toward the top of the page. This creates navigational paradoxes as their consistent actions lead to inconsistent results.
The Sensory Cue: Each time the maze shifts, describe a subtle, non-visual clue: "You feel a faint tremor through the soles of your boots and hear a deep, groaning sound, like ancient wood straining." This is the key that allows players to connect their actions to the world's reaction and solve the puzzle.

Random Encouter: 
use the info below if players spend too long in one place the goal is to make it clear a long rest attempt would be fatal, and that they must keep moving. 
Description: What was once a straight stone path to the grove's center has become a shifting maze of living hedges. The thorny walls move slowly but constantly, creating new passages while closing others. Ancient stone markers with Kynareth's symbol still stand, but they're covered in corrupted moss.
The Maze Challenge: The party must navigate through the ever-changing maze to reach the center. This requires either:
Magic Approach: Magic roll (Hard -2) to sense the natural flow and predict how the maze will shift
Nature Knowledge: Guile roll (Hard -2) to understand how the corrupted plants move and work with their patterns
Brute Force: Agility roll (Hard -2) to quickly dash through gaps before they close
Fire Solution: Characters with fire magic can burn through hedge walls, but this alerts all creatures in the grove (+1 enemy in remaining encounters)
Failure Consequence: Getting lost in the maze triggers an ambush. Animated thorny vines burst from the hedge walls to attack the party.
